text: Malin Gut (born 1 August 2000) is a Swiss footballer who plays as a midfielder for Arsenal and for the Switzerland women's national team. ==Career== Gut has been capped for the Switzerland national team, appearing for the team during the 2019 FIFA Women's World Cup qualifying cycle. In July 2020, Gut signed for Arsenal after playing for Grasshopper Club Zürich. Gut made her Arsenal debut on 6 September 2020.
